onmouth]] Roman fort\n*[[Caer Gybi (fort)|Caer Gybi]], [[Anglesey]] Roman fort\n*[[Caerleon]], Newport, [[Monmouthshire]] Roman fortress and amphitheatre\n*[[Caersws Roman Forts]], [[Powys]]\n*[[Caerwent]], [[Monmouthshire]]. Roman town - the only one in Wales\n*[[Cardiff Roman Fort]]\n*[[Cold Knap]], Barry\n*[[Cowbridge Roman Town]] probably Bovium\n*[[Dolaucothi Gold Mines]], [[Carmarthenshire]]. Fort, settlement and museum.\n*[[Gelligaer]] small Roman fort\n*[[Gateholm]], [[Pembrokeshire]]\n*[[Llan Ffestiniog]], [[Gwynedd]] fort & amphitheatre\n*[[Luentinum]] Roman fort at [[Pumsaint]], [[Carmarthenshire]]\n*[[Moridunum (Carmarthen)|Moridunum]], [[Carmarthen]]\n*[[Nidum]], Neath, [[Glamorgan]]. Roman fort\n*[[Penydarren]], [[Merthyr Tydfil]]. Roman fort\n*[[Sarn Helen]] [[Roman road]]\n*[[Segontium Roman Fort]], [[Caernarfon]]\n*[[Usk]] [[Burrium]] early legionary base\n*[[Y Gaer, Brecon]] cavalry base\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of Roman place names in Britain]]\n* [[List of Latin place names in Britain]]\n* [[Roman Britain]]\n* [[Sub-Roman Britain]]\n* [[Roman Scotland]]\n* [[Roman Wales]]\n* [[Romano-Celtic Temple]]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=1m055UlJWsufwKQwGAxMR6iI5-6M&ll=54.660386805844084%2C-1.0321488720702519&z=7 Roman sites in Britain KMZ file]\n\n{{Major towns of Roman Britain}}\n{{Roman visitor sites in the UK}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Roman sites in the United Kingdom| Roman sites]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "Douglal", "label": "safe", "comment": "Lutudarum added", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_sites_in_Great_Britain"}
{"title_page": "71 Tauri", "text_new": "{{short description|Star in the constellation Taurus}}\n{{Starbox begin\n | name = 71 Tauri\n}}\n{{Starbox observe\n | epoch = [[J2000.0]]\n | constell = [[Taurus (constellation)|Taurus]]\n | ra = {{RA|04|26|20.77302}}<ref name=GaiaDR2/>\n | dec = {{DEC|+15|37|05.7885}}<ref name=GaiaDR2/>\n | appmag_v = +4.48<ref name=\"MERMILLIOD\"/>\n}}\n{{Starbox character \n | class = F0&nbsp;V<ref name=Mullan2000/>\n | b-v = +0.25<ref name=\"MERMILLIOD\"/>\n | u-b = +0.13<ref name=\"MERMILLIOD\"/>\n | variable = [[Delta Scuti variable|\u03b4 Sct]]<ref name=Samus2017/>\n}}\n{{Starbox astrometry\n | radial_v = +38.3<ref name=rgcrv/>\n | prop_mo_ra = +85.393<ref name=GaiaDR2/>\n | prop_mo_dec = \u221214.869<ref name=GaiaDR2/>\n | parallax = 22.4141\n | p_error = 0.4969\n | parallax_footnote = <ref name=GaiaDR2/>\n | absmag_v = 1.10<ref name=aaa361_614/>\n}}\n{{Starbox detail\n | mass = 1.94<ref name=aaa361_614/>\n | radius = 3.34<ref name=Mullan2000/>\n | luminosity = \n | gravity = 3.73<ref name=David2015/>\n | temperature = 7,543<ref name=Mullan2000/>\n | metal_fe = \n | rotation = 14.2<ref name=aaa361_614/>&nbsp;d\n | rotational_velocity = 192<ref name=aaa361_614/>\n | age_myr = 966<ref name=David2015/>\n}}\n{{Starbox catalog\n | names = {{odlist | name=Polyxo{{citation needed|date=March 2017}} | F=71 Tau | V=V777 Tau | BD=+15\u00b0625 | HD=28052 | HIP=20713 | HR=1394 | SAO=93932 | GC=5375 }}<ref name=SIMBAD/>\n}}\n{{Starbox reference\n | Simbad=71+Tau\n}}\n{{Starbox end}}\n\n'''71 Tauri''' is a suspected [[triple star]]<ref name=Eggleton2008/> system in the [[zodiac]] [[constellation]] [[Taurus (constellation)|Taurus]], located 146&nbsp;[[light year]]s from the Sun.<ref name=GaiaDR2/> It is visible to the naked eye as a faint, yellow-white hued star with an [[apparent visual magnitude]] of +4.48.<ref name=\"MERMILLIOD\"/> The star is moving further away from the Earth with a heliocentric [[radial velocity]] of +38&nbsp;km/s.<ref name=rgcrv/> It is a member of the [[Hyades (star cluster)|Hyades open cluster]].<ref name=Simon2000/>\n\nThe primary component is an [[F-type main-sequence star]] with a [[stellar classification]] of F0&nbsp;V.<ref name=Mullan2000/> It is a [[Delta Scuti variable]] with an [[amplitude]] of 0.02 in magnitude and a frequency of 0.16&nbsp;d<sup>\u22121</sup>.<ref name=Samus2017/> This star has about 1.94<ref name=aaa361_614/> times the [[mass of the Sun]] and 3.34<ref name=Mullan2000/> times the [[Sun's radius]]. It has a [[projected rotational velocity]] of 192&nbsp;km s<sup>\u22121</sup>, for an estimated rotation period of 14.2 days.<ref name=aaa361_614/> Extreme ultraviolet flares have been observed coming from this star's hot [[stellar corona|corona]],<ref name=Mullan2000/> and it is the second brightest [[X-ray astronomy|X-ray source]] in the Hyades.<ref name=Simon2000/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=GaiaDR2>{{cite DR2|3312759303911629952}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=aaa361_614>{{citation\n | last1=Pizzolato | first1=N. | last2=Maggio | first2=A.\n | last3=Sciortino | first3=S.\n | title=Evolution of X-ray activity of 1-3 M<sub>sun</sub> late-type stars in early post-main-sequence phases\n | journal=Astronomy and Astrophysics\n | volume=361 | pages=614\u2013628 | date=September 2000\n | bibcode=2000A&A...361..614P | postscript=. }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Mullan2000>{{citation \n | title=Extreme-Ultraviolet Flares in an F2 Star \n | last1=Mullan | first1=D. J. | last2=Mathioudakis | first2=M. \n | journal=The Astrophysical Journal\n | volume=544 | issue=1 | pages=475\u2013480 | date=November 2000\n | doi=10.1086/317202 | bibcode=2000ApJ...544..475M \n | postscript=. }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=SIMBAD>{{citation\n | title=71 Tau  -- Variable Star of delta Sct type\n | work=SIMBAD Astronomical Database\n | publisher=[[Centre de Donn\u00e9es astronomiques de Strasbourg]]\n | url=http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/sim-id.pl?protocol=html&Ident=71+tauri\n | accessdate=2007-01-25 }}</