boney%20m%20nielsen%20soundscan&f=false|title=Pink's latest greatest hit|publisher=Billboard |date=2 October 2010}}</ref>|access-date=12 April 2018} |relyear=2001|certyear=2006}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Awards ceremony\n!Award\n!Results\n|-\n||2002\n|[[MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n|Best Song\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2002\n|[[MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|Best Female Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2002\n|[[MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|Best Dance Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2002\n|[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|Favorite Song\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2002\n|[[Q Awards]]\n|Best Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2003\n|[[Grammy Awards]]\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]]\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Shirley Bassey version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Get the Party Started\n| cover      = Shirley Bassey - Get the Party Started (single).png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shirley Bassey]]\n| album      = [[Get the Party Started (album)|Get the Party Started]]\n| released   = July 23, 2007\n| format     = [[CD single]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2006\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Vocal music|vocal]]\n| length     = 4:02\n| label      = Lock Stock and Barrel\n| writer     = [[Linda Perry]]\n| producer   = Catherine Feeney, Nikki Lamborn, Chuck Norman, Bob Kraushaar\n| prev_title = [[The Living Tree (song)|The Living Tree]]\n| prev_year  = 2007\n| next_title = [[Big Spender]]\n| next_year  = 2007\n}}\n[[Shirley Bassey]] recorded a cover for a [[spy]]-themed 2006 [[Marks & Spencer]] Christmas television advertising campaign.<ref>Woods, Sarah. [https://archive.today/20130102173343/http://www.brandrepublic.com/bulletins/br/article/602985/shirley-bassey-stars-bondstyle-marks-spencer-ad/ \"Shirley Bassey stars in Bond-style Marks & Spencer ad\"]. Brand Republic. November 6, 2006.</ref> Her version became a [[cult hit]]<ref name=TheGuardian>Macpherson, Alex. [http://music.guardian.co.uk/reviews/story/0,,2108431,00.html \"Reviews - Pop CD - Dame Shirley Bassey, Get the Party Started\"]. ''[[The Guardian]]''. June 22, 2007.</ref> and was included on her 2007 album, also titled ''[[Get the Party Started (album)|Get the Party Started]]''. ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote, \"Bassey is the only singer alive who could take the bouncing, enthusiastic [[contemporary R&B|R&B]] of the original Get the Party Started and turn it into a grand, imperious swoop worthy of a [[James Bond music#Main title themes|Bond theme]]; it's a terrific cover version, even if it perhaps didn't quite merit the album attached to it.\"<ref name=TheGuardian/>\n\nOn 13 January 2008, Bassey's version was used in the opening sequence to the [[ITV1]] series ''[[Dancing on Ice]]''. It was also used in the promo for Cycle 4 of ''[[Australia's Next Top Model]]'', and Bassey's version charted at number 47 in the UK<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/What%20Hurts%20The%20Most|title=Official Charts Company - The Chart Archive|website=[[Official Charts Company]]}}</ref> and ended at the [[Billboard Year-End|Billboard Year-End Charts]] at number forty-three in the Hot Dance Club Plays Tracks of the year, having peaked at number 3 in April 2008.<ref>http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2008/dance-club-songs</ref><ref>http://www.billboard.com/music/shirley-bassey/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs</ref> The track was used again in 2010 for the opening credits of the spy-spoof movie ''[[Cats & Dogs: The Revenge of Kitty Galore]]''.  The track was also used for 2015 commercial of [[Honda Stepwgn]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Honda\uff5cHonda Movie Channel\uff5c\u30b9\u30c6\u30c3\u30d7 \u30ef\u30b4\u30f3 - \u300cARROW\u300d\u7bc7|url=http://www.honda.co.jp/movie/201504/stepwgn01/|website=Honda Japan|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Track listings and formats===\n'''[[United Kingdom|UK]] [[Compact Disc|CD]] single'''\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Radio edit) \u2013 3:08\n# \"Get The Party Started\" \u2013 4:02\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (NorthXNorthWest Club mix) \u2013 7:21\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Fugitives Coming Up mix) \u2013 5:34\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Flip & Fill remix) \u2013 5:58\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Music video) \u2013 4:00\n\n'''[[United States|US]] [[Digital data|Digital]] single'''\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Chris Cox Club mix) \u2013 8:45 \n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Chris Cox Dub mix) \u2013 8:05\n# \"Get The Party Started\" (Chris Cox Radio mix) \u2013 3:49\n\n==Cover versions and in pop culture==\n* [[David Cassidy]] performed the song as fictional Vegas performer Boone Vincent in the \"[[Hot Tub (Malcolm in the Middle episode)|Vegas]]\" episode of the TV series ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/malcolm-in-the-middle/vegas/episode/263184/summary.html|title=Malcolm in the Middle: Vegas episode on TV.com|publisher=TV.com|accessdate=2009-10-20}}</ref>\n* [[Stretch Arm Strong]] covered the song on the first [[Punk Goes Pop]] compilation.\n* Dan Winter did a trance cover of the song as a single in 2008.\n* Hits For Kids 4, Hits For Kids Pop Party 2 and Hits For Kids Ultimate Party Hits\n* Girl authority's self titled debut album-the cover features Party Katie\n\n==Appearances in other media==\n* In early 2002, Pink teamed up with [[Bally Total Fitness]] to promote Bally Total Fitness memberships. The title of the advertising campaign was \"Get This Body Started\", and in early 2002 there were several Bally Total Fitness commercials in the United States that used the Pink song.\n* The track was used extensively by the [[NBA]] during the 2002&ndash;2003 season. For the Finals, ABC used the song as the [[National Basketball Association music|introduction music in 2003]].\n* Use on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' when [[Paris Hilton]] appeared on the show once.\n* Used in ''[[Pump It Up (video game)|Pump it Up]]: The PREX 3'', a rhythm dancing arcade game.\n* The Shirley Bassey version of the song is also considered the official anthem for the 2010 sequel, ''[[Cats & Dogs: The Revenge of Kitty Galore]]''.\n* The song was made [[Complete list of downloadable songs for the Rock Band series|available to download]] on April 17, 2012 for play in [[Rock Band 3]] Basic and PRO mode utilizing real guitar / bass guitar, and MIDI compatible electronic drum kits / keyboards plus vocal harmonies.\n* The song appeared in the second ''[[Daria]]'' TV movie and series finale ''[[Is It College Yet?]]'' during Lindy's party.\n* The song appeared in ''[[South Park]]'' season 18 episode 2 in ''[[Gluten Free Ebola]]''.\n* The song appeared in the pilot episode of ''[[The Middle (TV series)|The Middle]]''.\n* The song appeared in ''[[The Simpsons]]'' season 26 episode 17 in ''[[Waiting for Duffman]]''\n* The song appeared in \u201c[[Black-ish]]\u201d season 1 episode 3 in \u201cThe Nod\u201d.\n* The song appeared in ''[[Pitch Perfect 3]]'' during the singing in the movie.\n* The song appeared in ''[[The Mindy Project]]'' season 6 episode 3 \"May Divorce Be With You\" during a karaoke scene.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Romanian Top 100 number ones of the 2000s]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{youtube|NZZ5VO97ix8|\"Get the Party Started\" music video}}\n\n{{Pink singles}}\n{{Shirley Bassey}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Get The Party Started}}\n[[Category:2001 singles]]\n[[Category:2002 singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Dave Meyers (director)]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Romania]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:UK R&B Singles Chart number-o